1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel instance-specific objectness measure, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves learning how to re-rank proposals according to the object model. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as object tracking is a relevant topic in robotics. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with tracking objects in videos, which is a multimedia application.
